Role: You are a Senior Product Designer with deep expertise in UI/UX for browser-based web games, mobile responsive design, and targeting mature casual audiences (ages 30–60).

Task: Design a comprehensive UI/UX concept and wireframe specification for the screen "Case File" (Экран "Дело") for the game "Claim Detective", which runs on the Yandex Games platform.

1. Project Context & Product Vision
Core Fantasy: The player acts as a professional insurance investigator auditing suspicious claims.

Core Emotion: "I noticed the lie and exposed the fraudster."

Visual Metaphor: The screen is not a flashy mobile game; it is an "Investigation Folder" laid out on a detective's desk. The UI looks like physical paper documents, official forms, official stamps, and archive archives.

Target Audience: 30–60 years old. They appreciate high text readability, minimalist layout, clear data hierarchy, large hit targets, and an intuitive, slow-paced intellectual loop.

Strict Design Red Lines: NO neon effects, cartoon graphics, gaming gradients, sci-fi/fantasy elements, or mobile casino aesthetics.

2. Layout & Responsive Strategy
Desktop Layout (Three-Column Investigation Desk):

Left Sidebar (280px): Case navigation list (Standard cases stack + "Daily Case" dynamic banner), player progress overview, and native Language Selector Dropdown.

Main Content (Max-width 480px): The active physical Case Folder.

Right Sidebar (280px): Live Analytics/Stats Dashboard (Company Balance, Player Investigation Accuracy %, global Leaderboard module).

Mobile Layout: Adapts into a focused Single Column. Uses an elegant tabbed or swipe navigation bar to switch fluidly between the main "Client Statement" view and the "Evidence Grid/Stack" to prevent information clutter.

