4. Step-by-Step UI Flow to Map out
Case Selection: Highlighting the distinct visuals between a standard grey case folder and the premium Daily Case folder (gold accents, urgent stamp effect).

Reviewing Statement: Designing the top folder sheet containing Client Photo ID, Personal Bio, and the structured written narrative story block.

The Investigation Layer: A dedicated grid area displaying diverse physical evidence artifacts (Receipts/Invoices, maps with GPS text coordinates, polaroid-styled Photo files, and tabular Chat Logs).

The Stamping Interaction: A detailed mock of the Full-Screen Modal overlay when an evidence file is clicked. It must include the large actionable toggle button "Mark as Contradiction". Show the visual transformation when active (a retro ink stamp texture overlaying the document stating "ПРОТИВОРЕЧИЕ / CONTRADICTION").

The Verdict Panel: Layout of the permanent "Approve Claim" (Success Green) and "Reject Claim" (Deep Professional Red) buttons.

The Result & Breakdown Sheet: A post-decision overlay displaying a dynamic resolution stamp ("CASE CLOSED / FRAUD EXPOSED" or "INVESTIGATOR ERROR"), an incremental breakdown progress bar mapping how much of the reward was unlocked via exact evidence discovery, and an administrative textual breakdown explaining the true solution logic.

5. Expected Output Delivery
Please generate a comprehensive product design specification sheet for a React TailwindCSS engineer, including:

Low-Fidelity Wireframe: Textual ASCII or structural layout matrix mapping out the positions of sections on Desktop vs Mobile screens.

Mid-Fidelity Wireframe Description: Structural specifications, spacing guidelines, padding allocations, typography scale hierarchy recommendations (e.g., matching a high-contrast sans-serif like Inter or a professional serif like IBM Plex Serif).

Component Interface States Matrix: Define explicit design tokens and styling shifts for elements across states: Default, Hover, Active/Selected (Stamped), and Disabled.

Micro-animations Specification: Provide guidelines for smooth transitions using Framer Motion (e.g., card lifting up effects, smooth document slide-outs, ink stamp scaling dampeners).

Proceed with generating the layout specifications in an analytical, structured, and developer-ready format.